                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Gleysteen, Culver: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Dairen</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Paddock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dairen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-28T19:00:00+09:00"
                            >May 28, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 30—7:31 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>162. Consulate has no details to add to its 154, May 23 re Soviet note re
                    Gleysteen detention. ReDeptel 67, May 23, received today.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 162; repeated Moscow 93, Nanking 117, Canton 61.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paddock</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
